EON Capital Said to Accept Resignation of Bank CEO Lor

-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 
2011-02-24T06:46:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/eon-capital-said-to-accept-resignation-of-bank-ceo-lor-correct-.html
(Corrects spelling of Hong Leong Bank shareholder in second
paragraph.)  EON Bank Bhd. Chief Executive
Officer Michael Lor has resigned, according to a person familiar
with the matter who couldn’t be named as the information is
still confidential. His resignation was accepted by the board of  EON Capital Bhd ., the Malaysian bank’s parent company, the
person said.  Shareholders last September approved a 5.06 billion-ringgit
takeover offer for EON Capital by  Hong Leong Bank Bhd .,
controlled by billionaire Quek Leng Chan. Completion is
currently subject to a legal challenge.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chong Pooi Koon in Kuala Lumpur at 
 pchong17@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Barry Porter at 
 bporter10@bloomberg.net  